    thinking: "**Designing Binaural Beats App**\n\nI\'m currently focused on the core architecture for this highly potent and modular binaural beats app. My primary concern right now is achieving maximum tonal variability. Specifically, I am planning how to create a system that can smoothly shift binaural tones at the 30-second interval the user mentioned. The goal is to provide a wide range of sound that still maintains a high quality of sound.\n\n\n**Assessing Feature Integration**\n\nI\'ve decided to refine the core focus to client-side state management for now, given the user\'s initial requirements for modular binaural beat generation. I\'m exploring the potential of integrating Gemini API as a psychoacoustic assistant. This could allow for custom meditation prompts, frequency set suggestions, and binaural audio recipes, which enhances the app\'s modularity and potency in terms of function!\n\n\n**Refining AI Guidance**\n\nI\'m now thinking about building a streamlined AI guide, maybe calling it \"Session Generator\". Gemini integration seems ideal for custom presets and psychoacoustic insights. The goal is to create a Web Audio API-based app with custom visualizers, frequency control, a timer, and 30-second cycles. I\'ll check `gemini-api` patterns and also consider `image-generation` for visuals and `shadcn-ui` for UI components.\n\n\n"
