  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Defining Potent Binaural Beats**\n\nI\'m focusing on \"very potent and modular binaural beats\" for the app. The user\'s need for beats that change every 30 seconds is a key consideration to maintain the psychoacoustic effect and avoid brain adaptation. This requirement really excites me.\n\n\n**Designing the Audio Engine**\n\nI\'m now diving into the Web Audio API to build the binaural audio engine. I\'m focusing on creating left and right channels with adjustable frequency offsets to generate the binaural beats, like 200Hz vs 210Hz for a 10Hz beat. The modulation needs to be \"potent\" and shift every 30 seconds to prevent habituation. Visualizers showing frequencies and waveforms are important. I\'m brainstorming preset programs like \"Deep Focus\" and \"Stress Relief\".\n\n\n**Refining Transitions and Ambience**\n\nI\'m making the 30-second frequency shifts seamless, using smooth sweeps with `exponentialRampToValueAtTime`. It feels very professional. Adding ambient soundscapes (rain, space wind, etc.) synthesised locally with Web Audio API is a must for a fully craft. I\'m focusing on dynamic oscillators and noise generators to make this happen, avoiding heavy assets and ensuring seamless performance.\n\n\n**Integrating AI and Customization**\n\nI\'m now integrating AI to generate custom binaural beat programs based on user text input. I\'m focusing on user prompts like \"I have a physics exam in 2 hours, I need maximum concentration but I am anxious\". The system will use Gemini to analyze the text and return a personalized JSON program with frequency targets, modulations, and neuroscience explanations. It\'s a huge step towards true modularity!\n\n\n**Structuring the Interface**\n\nI\'m now outlining the application\'s user interface with a clear dashboard design. I\'m focusing on components like \"Psicoacoustic Timeline\", \"Wave Control Panel\", \"Ambient Synthesizer\" and \"AI Session Designer\". I\'m planning a beautiful layout to show this. Also, I will use standard HTML Canvas and requestAnimationFrame for a real-time visualizer that shows frequencies, waveforms, or abstract breathing/entrainment geometries. The `@google/genai` SDK will be incorporated for personalized wave generation.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will view the `metadata.json` file to prepare for updating the application name and metadata to match the user\'s requested modular binaural beats application."
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 9
      nanos: 216256087
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
