soidal offset to give a bit of movement. The right channel is visualized using an indigo/violet color that is overlaid over the left channel. I\'m also now implementing the drawing logic for both channels.\n\n\n**Finalizing Waveform Drawing**\n\nI\'m now putting the finishing touches on the waveform visuals. I\'ve integrated a sinusoidal offset to create slight movement in the emerald-colored left channel waveform, and an indigo/violet overlay for the right channel. I\'ve also added small HUD overlay text, displaying live frequency offsets for each channel using monospace font.\n\n\n**Optimizing Frequency Overlays**\n\nI\'ve just implemented the HUD overlay text, which displays live frequency offsets for each channel in a monospace font. I\'ve placed the channel frequency data on the top and the binaural beat frequency at the bottom. The visual is working, and the text is responsive. I\'ve re-examined line 695.\n\n\n**Refining Modular Time Logic**\n\nI\'m now integrating the time engine with the modular structure. I\'ve placed the `setInterval` call inside a `useEffect` hook, to sync with `isPlaying`, `isModulationEnabled`, and the modulation steps. Also, the timer now correctly advances to the next modulation step when the countdown hits zero. The cleanup function clears the interval.\n\n\n"
