erified the logic that properly manages the frequency refresh. The integration is seamless.\n\n\n**Reviewing the Array Data**\n\nI\'m now carefully reviewing the data array population logic within the visualization. I\'ve re-examined how the `dataArrayL` and `dataArrayR` are updated based on the `isPlaying` state and the presence of analysers. I\'m verifying the placeholder wave generation when playback is paused, and how the values are used for drawing. I am satisfied with the current state.\n\n\n**Validating the Drawing**\n\nI\'m now zeroing in on the drawing context within `/components/BinauralBeatsApp.tsx`. I am confirming the grid lines are drawn with correct spacing, and the sacred mandala\'s pulsation is mapped to the binaural frequency accurately. The radial gradient, pulsing with the breath, should be evident. I have not identified problems with the visual design.\n\n\n**Enhancing the Hexagram**\n\nI\'m now deep-diving into the hexagram pattern, confirming its rotation and visual layering with the other shapes. I\'m making sure the slow rotation of the hexagram is smooth and the color changes sync with `isPlaying`. The interlaced triangle\'s appearance is also of keen interest to me, because the goal is an appealing visualization.\n\n\n**Refining the Waveform**\n\nI\'m now zeroing in on the channel data\'s visual representation, specifically the left channel. I\'m scrutinizing the emerald green ribbon\'s parameters: line width, color, and how the amplitude impacts the wave\'s vertical position. The domain mapping, high center shift, and normalization factor are also being evaluated for accurate audio-visual mapping.\n\n\n**Adjusting the Offset**\n\nI\'m now carefully examining the offset within the right channel\'s wave drawing logic. Specifically, I\'m checking the value `(Math.sin(i * 0.05 - timeSec * 2) * (isPlaying ? -8 : -2))` and making sure that the offset changes visually with the audio. I am also making sure that the domain mapping and amplitude no