n the input range and display to ensure the UI updates correctly. I\'ve been considering how to update the `activeProgramName` and `aiExplanation` when the frequency is manually changed, maintaining the minimalist interface\'s clean look.\n\n\n**Evaluating Modulation Button Design**\n\nI\'m now carefully evaluating the modulation button design, specifically the conditional styling based on `isModulationEnabled`. I\'m focusing on the visual cues to differentiate active and paused states, ensuring the UI/UX is clear and consistent. I\'m testing the color scheme to guarantee the readability and adherence to the minimalist aesthetic. I am aiming to ensure clarity.\n\n\n**Integrating AI Functionality**\n\nI\'m now integrating the AI mind architect prompt and button. I\'m focusing on UI elements for the text input, sintonizar button, and error handling. I\'m incorporating loading states and error messages, ensuring a smooth and responsive user experience. I\'m striving to keep the design sleek and efficient, minimizing any unnecessary visual distractions.\n\n\n**Comparing Code Changes**\n\nI\'m now comparing the current code chunk against the original structure to check the new layout. I\'m focusing on the integration of active program data, AI explanations, and modulation stage info. I\'m looking at how these elements fit with the design, ensuring they\'re visually balanced and minimalist. My aim is a seamless transition and excellent user experience.\n\n\n"
